Subject: dxf: hex-encode binary TF chunks (group codes 310-319)

FIELD_TF with a 310 group code (PROXY_ENTITY.proxy_data) went through the
string path (VALUE_TV), emitting the raw bytes — including the codepage
conversion for r2007+ — instead of the hex encoding DXF requires for
binary chunk groups. Readers reject the resulting file ("invalid binary
data"). Route binary chunk groups through VALUE_BINARY.

The previously unused `len` macro argument now compiles, exposing a
-Werror=pointer-sign in OLE2FRAME's strlen call; cast it.

Real-world reproducer: 27 MB r2013 cadastre drawing with partially
decoded ACAD_PROXY_ENTITYs (found via IngeCAD's real-file bench).
Applies on top of 0001 (upstream af67061c backport). Also present in
master as of f280466.

--- a/src/out_dxf.c
+++ b/src/out_dxf.c
@@ -678,7 +678,18 @@ dxf_print_rd (Bit_Chain *dat, BITCODE_RD value, int dxf)
 #define FIELD_RLL(nam, dxf) FIELDG (nam, RLL, dxf)
 #define FIELD_MC(nam, dxf) FIELDG (nam, MC, dxf)
 #define FIELD_MS(nam, dxf) FIELDG (nam, MS, dxf)
-#define FIELD_TF(nam, len, dxf) VALUE_TV (_obj->nam, dxf)
+/* Group codes 310-319 hold binary chunks: hex-encode them. Writing them
+   through the string path (VALUE_TV) emits raw bytes — invalid DXF that
+   readers reject (e.g. PROXY_ENTITY.proxy_data via FIELD_TF). */
+#define FIELD_TF(nam, len, dxf)                                               \
+  {                                                                           \
+    if ((dxf) >= 310 && (dxf) <= 319)                                         \
+      {                                                                       \
+        VALUE_BINARY (_obj->nam, len, dxf)                                    \
+      }                                                                       \
+    else                                                                      \
+      VALUE_TV (_obj->nam, dxf)                                               \
+  }
 #define FIELD_TFF(nam, len, dxf) VALUE_TV (_obj->nam, dxf)
 #define FIELD_TV(nam, dxf)                                                    \
   if (dxf)                                                                    \
--- a/src/dwg.spec
+++ b/src/dwg.spec
@@ -5954,7 +5954,7 @@ DWG_ENTITY (OLE2FRAME)
 #ifdef IS_DXF
   // via dwg_decode_ole2() from the first 0x80 bytes in data
   FIELD_BS (oleversion, 70); //  always 2
-  FIELD_TF (oleclient, strlen (_obj->oleclient), 3);
+  FIELD_TF (oleclient, strlen ((char *)_obj->oleclient), 3);
   FIELD_3BD (pt1, 10);  // upper left
   FIELD_3BD (pt2, 11);  // lower right
 #endif
